casebody.data:
576 A.2d 219 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. Ralph WEISS. Misc. (Subtitle BV) No. 16,

Sept. Term, 1990.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. July 10, 1990.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the consent to disbarment filed by Ralph Weiss in accordance with Maryland Rule BV 12 d 2, and the written recommendation of Bar Counsel, it is this 10th day of July, 1990

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Ralph Weiss be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Ralph Weiss from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule BV13, shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
